    • DefaultParameterizedType

      public DefaultParameterizedType(Type ownerType, Type rawType, Type actualTypeArgument)
      Creates a new DefaultParameterizedType.
      Parameters:
      ownerType - the Type that owns this DefaultParameterizedType; may be (and usually is) null
      rawType - the raw type; must not be null; is most commonly a Class as in all JDKs through at least 17 and as mandated currently by the Java Language Specification
      actualTypeArgument - the actual actual type argument of this DefaultParameterizedType; must not be null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if rawType or actualTypeArgument is null
      IllegalArgumentException - if rawType is an instance of Class and the length of the array returned by its Class.getTypeParameters() method is not 1

    • DefaultParameterizedType

      public DefaultParameterizedType(Type ownerType, Type rawType, Type... actualTypeArguments)
      Creates a new DefaultParameterizedType.
      Parameters:
      ownerType - the Type that owns this DefaultParameterizedType; may be (and usually is) null
      rawType - the raw type; must not be null; is most commonly a Class as in all JDKs through at least 17 and as mandated currently by the Java Language Specification
      actualTypeArguments - the actual actual type arguments of this DefaultParameterizedType; may be null in which case a zero-length array will be used instead; will be cloned if non-null and if its length is greater than 0
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if rawType is null
      IllegalArgumentException - if rawType is an instance of Class and the length of the array returned by its Class.getTypeParameters() method is not the same as the length of the actualTypeArguments array (or 0 if the actualTypeArguments array is null)

    • of

      public static final DefaultParameterizedType of(ParameterizedType parameterizedType)
      If the supplied ParameterizedType is a DefaultParameterizedType, returns it; otherwise creates a new DefaultParameterizedType with the supplied ParameterizedType's owner type, raw type and type arguments and returns it.
      Parameters:
      parameterizedType - the ParameterizedType to effectively copy (or return); must not be null
      Returns:
      a non-null DefaultParameterizedType
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if parameterizedType is null
      Idempotency:
      This method is idempotent but not deterministic (in that it may return a new DefaultParameterizedType with each invocation).
      Nullability:
      This method never returns null.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.
